caption: I got the Bruins and it’s the best iced tea I’ve ever had!

Excellent service and food today.  Staff was very accommodating on food allergies and specialty drinks were very flavorful.  Banh mi was legit as well and my girls loved the crepe as well.  Highly recommend as a light lunch fare with great drinks.

Stopped here for some Banh mi and coffee. The bread was crunchy and the veggies were fresh. I really enjoyed the banh mi but I wish they left the seeds in on the jalapeños to keep that spice. The strawberry crepe was really yummy but I felt like they used too many strawberries. Every bite I took had a strawberry in it which is good but not something I like. If you are the mood for some Vietnamese cuisine give this place a try it's great!

Waited 25 minutes to get a sandwich for takeout while other people got their drinks/food. When I asked where my sandwich was, the lady at the front said she saw it made but they never wrapped it or called my name. Waited another 10 minutes after that to get my food. Not sure if the kitchen just had a bad day, but prepare to wait around.
The Phin 50/50 is the greatest drink I have ever had! 100 percent would recommend!
I cannot say enough good things about this place. Everyone that works there is so friendly, the coffee is out of this world, and the food is top notch.
Iced coffee is amazing, we had the shrimp and tofu bahn mi and they were unbelievable. Perfect bread, super tasty. Staff is really nice. Can't wait to come back!!
One of my favorite cafes in Boston. The matcha latte is great and the staff members are friendly too.

I am thankful that they have a vegan option for banh mi lovers like me. It tastes almost exactly like the real thing. I’m also thankful that they offer almond milk for their drinks. It’s a bit far from where I live but I like to stop by once in a while.

Im heard about new management couple weeks ago and I wanna stop by try it. OMG I'm blowing my head because everything. The owners and the staffs super friendly. I was very impressed with their drinks and crepes menu. Hand down for the Cafe Sua Da ( coffee latte) and Tuscan Chicken crepe and im in love with that. That’s perfect combo to start my day. Im definitely be back soon to try everything that have on the menu. Best Vietnamese coffee and crepe in the town!!!!!  Update: the matcha buns are amazinggggg
Coffee bun had a beautiful crunchy top with a mild coffee flavor but bad proofing (collapsed middle that was incredibly dense and slightly gummy). Very pricey ($4 each).

Very nice vibes with both the people and restaurant décor. Their coffee options are on the pricey side – similar to specialty lattes from Starbucks. But my Vietnamese coffee latte was very good (maybe a tad too sweet), as was the sweet cream pastry I got. Also tried their BBQ pork banh mi (my favorite kind). It was mid-range – their sauce was a bit too sweet for me. And the veggies weren’t as crisp or as tasty as I’ve had them elsewhere.
Love their coffee and coffee buns.
Fantastic authentic Vietnamese food. Some of the best i have had.
Amazing coffee and crepes ! Highly recommend to everyone :)
my favorite place to go for crepes, coffee, pastries, pho, and more! i can't get enough of it and can't wait to go back!
The nicest owners, tasty food, and strong coffee.
My favorite local spot!! Food and drinks are great with a welcoming atmosphere

So happy to see a Vietnamese cafe in this area, this is a much needed addition to the Fenway area! Their current menu includes a wide variety of coffee and tea with lots of Asian inspired flavors (including classic Vietnamese iced coffee as well as trendy drinks like dragon fruit and lemonade tea), delicious crepes that are upgraded from Neighborhood Cafe's old offerings, and best of all, authentic Vietnamese dishes like grilled pork vermicelli and classic banh mi sandwiches. I live close by and this is my favorite new place to eat.

I genuinely don’t understand the bad reviews because my experience was absolutely fantastic. Everyone working was super friendly and helpful! I got the 50/50 thanks to their recommendation and it was soooooo good. It is a combination of their oolong milk tea and the Vietnamese coffee. I loved that it wasn’t too sweet nor too milky. I’m glad I convinced my friends to drive 20min to this place because they loved it too.
Amazing coffee and food! Authentic Vietnamese coffee - try the iced cafe sua da and a classic banh mi! Great addition to the Fenway neighborhood and can’t wait to try everything else on their menu.
Great vietnamese coffee! Crepes were good as well and seems like the menu has been expanding.
The food, drinks, and atmosphere were amazing and the people who work here are so sweet!

I went to phinsta for the first time today for brunch and it was amazing. The service was some of the friendliness I’ve experienced. They were super sweet and I really appreciated it. The food is amazing, I got the cinnamon roll crepe. I pretty much finished it in a minute. Overall, the experience was 10/10 and I will definitely come back in the future.

My partner and I first discovered Phinista last month, and we went back twice in one week we had such an amazing experience. I’ve had both their Croque Madame and Sweet Caroline savory crepes, and they're absolutely delicious. They also have my favorite milk tea in Boston. The staff is always super friendly and helpful. When I stopped in this morning, I was recommend to try the Oolong Milk Tea for the first time, and I’m so glad it was suggested because I think it’s my new favorite :) thanks to everyone at Phinista for being so amazing!
Good taste of food.

Phinista Cafe is an excellent place to grab quick, affordable, and delicious meal! They have great service. I will definitely return, and can recommend either the Peach Cobbler or The Alaskan, though everything sounds delicious!
Always a pleasant experience when I come here! Can never go wrong with a good cup of coffee and an extraordinary service!

This is my go-to place for coffee. It is amazing and I fall in love more with each visit. The coffee is outstanding and the ambiance even more so. Phil is excellent to talk to, and I cannot imagine how difficult it must be in these times to stay afloat.  Pictured is the Iced Phin Mocha!! Highly recommend this and the Phin Sua!  PS: Avoid the rush hours if you can, the wait can be a little longer than what you'd expect, but worth the wait.

Thank you for the wonderful service that you have! Last Monday evening, I decided to unwind with my friends at your shop. We were so surprised when your staff served our order quickly. What's best about your shop is, you really got the taste of your customers. Bravo to all of you! You are strongly recommended!

Loved the atmosphere here! Staff were very friendly, patient, and answered all my questions. One of them even gave me a small cup of coffee on the side to see where my sweetness preference was. Coffee was delicious, strong, and had no leftover grounds at the bottom of my drink. Their peach cobbler crepe was delightful! Definitely coming back next time I'm in Boston!
"Portions are just right for brunch, though a bit small for the price."

This place has rebranded so I'm updating my review!  This place is super fun and super insta worthy! They have lots of outdoor seating and their indoor seating is well-spaced as well. Food and drink are excellent and service is quick too. We got our drinks easily within 5 minutes, despite arriving in the morning on Sunday for coffees/teas. Egg coffee was sweat and creamy, the berry matcha milk tea was beautiful and also very strongly matcha-flavored (in the best way), and the croque madame crepe was tasty without being overwhelmingly heavy.  Definitely recommend this place for a to-go or to-sit-outside snack and drink, and take a picture while you're at it!
Baum mi is amazing, cafe is super cute - I’ve been back like 4 times this month alone

This place is great! Had the pork banh mi which was delicious and the sauce was tasty. The black milk tea was fantastic and actually tasted like tea. The matcha lava cake, ube lava cake, and vanilla lava cake were all delicious and well done. The ambiance was nice and chill, great place to hang out with friends on a lowkey Friday night!  10/10 would recommend!
Nice spot for quality Cafe food. The service was very friendly and attentive. Prices are reasonable I would say.
So delicious crepe with nutella and strawberries
The coffee is out of this world. Delicious and creative flavor combinations. I love the Rose flavored latte. We've tried both the crepes and the bahn mi. Can't wait to go back to try the pho!

The best cold brew I’ve ever had. I knew it would be good because they value quality and good ingredients but I had no idea it would be this good! It is the smoothest cold brew I’ve ever had. It has an extremely rich and deep flavor almost like caramel but not sweet. Do yourself a favor and pop into this extremely cute coffee shop. I hear they also serve Vietnamese food for lunch and dinner but I haven’t tried it but I will be back soon for that as well

A wonderful addition to diversify the neighborhood. A minority-owned cafe that even continues the Crepe tradition from previous owners. Very warm and welcoming owner to both humans and pets!! I recommend the Viet iced coffee and cinnamon crepe!
Amazing teas and food

Awesome cafe with great food and nice atmosphere! I got the Tuscan Chicken crepe with a Milk 'n Jas and they were perfect for a weekday lunch. Crepe was super filling and even had leftovers! Milk 'n Jas was fragrant and had a good ratio of milk-to-tea. I visited in the late afternoon and there was plenty of seats on the patio and inside. Phinsta is a cute neighborhood spot that I could see myself studying at (when the pandemic ends) and might definitely become my new go-to crepe place!
I had the best cold brew with a splash of oat milk that I've enjoyed in ages. This place was bustling on a Saturday morning, and the crepes looked incredible!

I might be a bit obsessed with this place! :) The flavors Phinista team comes up with are out of this world and every coffee/chai/latte you'll go for, it will be amazing. The crepes are super tasty as well and I can't wait to try their lava cakes. Follow them on IG at your own risk! ☺️
Great local vietnamese/french style cafe. The crepes are great and you can get vietnamese coffee, milk tea and fruit teas.
You like Vietnamese coffee? Go here!
My favorite location for quality Cafe food. There was fast and courteous service. I can see why they have a lot of great reviews.
Best of luck for the new owner, I just miss the Neighbors I grew accustomed to.  Perhaps a future visit trying the new recipes will be great
Phinista is a must stop kind of place! Their Vietnamese iced coffee is amazing - it probably has the most authentic Viet coffee taste around here. Highly recommended!

Love the looks and vibe of this new cafe in Fenway. I was greeted and welcomed by the warm and polite staff. I ordered The Happy and the Alaskan crepe, my oh my was the crepe so delicious legit devoured it in 30 seconds!! If you love smoked salmon, I highly recommend this crepe, best thing ever! Next time I will visit the cafe earlier in the day so I can snag some of the other yummy drinks before it’s sold out! Check them out, you won’t disappointed!

Amazing staff and the crepes are delicious! The tea is unique and yummy. If you want Vietnamese coffee, the Cafe Sua Da is authentic!  High recommendations: -The salmon crepe is to DIE for -Milk Black Tea is great
Stopped by on my way to the ISG museum. Great cold brew, house sweetener was amazing. Met the new owner who was very welcoming and friendly. Highly suggest

I’m a Phinista fan before they open their coffee shop in Fenway. I’m in love with their coffees, especially cafe creme brulee. They used to have an awesome project that they gave out free coffees for health care workers. I can feel that the owners care about their customers with their hearts. I came to the shop today and ordered a cafe cream brulee which is bomb. I also had a “is this in heaven” crepe. It’s sooooo tasty and wonderful to start a day with. I hope that they will have their signature lava cake on the menu soon. Love this place.

Phinista’s Vietnamese Iced Coffee is a must try - so delicious! They use traditional Vietnamese coffee recipe which would help you wake instantly. I was very impressed with their drinks menu too, very creative with fresh, real, tasty ingredients. This place is never a wrong choice. Bad thing is that they haven’t opened many locations

My friend told me about this lovely place and I’m glad that I came. I got the Cafe Sua Da and Is this Heaven crepe, and it was so delicious. It was a perfect combo. Their crepe was sweet and fresh. Probably the best Viet coffee I’ve had, their cafe sua da is a must-try. The owner and staffs was super friendly and welcome, everything was perfect. I’m definitely gonna come back for the coffee and crepes. Highly recommend!!!
great little place, with great staff, and love the selection, gotta get there early to get that coconut coffee yummm.

I highly recommend the Is This Heaven crepe! Inside was strawberry and choco sauce along with custard creme and caramelized walnuts which I found out are actually made in-house. The crepe also paired nicely with a Cafe Creme Brulee! Such a new and refreshing place. The owners were also super friendly and welcoming! Will definitely be back to try other things on the menu.

I heard about the new management couple weeks ago and was able to try them yesterday. Their service was awesome, the owners and staffs were very nice and friendly. They still carry the vibe that Neighborhoods had but newer and younger. The Ca Phe Sua Da (Viet Latte) was a great kick for my morning and the CM crepe was so yummy.
This place is all about the details. The new management is awesome and has really added a cozy personal touch. The drinks will leave you speechless!!
Hand down for their coffee and crepe. I strongly recommend the cafe creme brulee and tuscan chicken crepe. Also their customer service is on point. I’ll come back soon for another desert and coffee.
Love everything about this place. Had the best matcha latte to start my day 🍵

wonderful and quaint establishment. great tasting crepes, strong cold brew (tastes like a good chocolate stout), nice atmosphere, and friendly folks running this business. owner was overly generous and chatted with me to give me recommendations of places to visit in the area. would definitely recommend to anyone in the fenway park area.
I got their Viet cafe mocha and it was honestly one of the best coffees i’ve ever had! So good!! 10/10 recommend :)

Best Vietnamese coffee in town. Their coffee bean is extremely fresh and different from all the coffee with fillers out there. The staffs are super friendly and helpful. My coffee lady, Erica is the sweatest one. Tuscan chicken crepe is wonderful with juicy chicken and all the fresh vegie!!! Love itttt
Love the Cafe Sua Da here. Im Vietnamese andhave to say this cafe is where you can find the best Vietnamese Coffee in Boston ❤️
Lovely crepe place with amazing drinks and phintastic people :)

Their Vietnamese iced coffee is TO DIE FOR! I couldn’t be happier this cafe has found a home in Fenway— incredibly high quality food and drink, friendly and kind owners, and overall my new favorite way to survive working from home.
My favorite place for tasty Cafe food. i'll return family next time. this place has a nice design.
The complete package. Crepes, both sweet and savory, were fantastic. Cappuccino was perfect, and I can’t wait to try their other drinks next time. Full crepe menu will be available next month!

Excited for what this place brings to the community.  Glossing over Boston Coffee’s 2 star review all I could sense was the immense loyalty and love they had for Neighborhoods Cafe.  As someone who has been following Phinista and their journey up to this point I can say, they have a different story to tell and we should come to understand that not every place starts off at 100% especially when it comes to building a relationship with the community. (You wouldn’t think that girl at the other side of the cafe is your soulmate, without getting to know them first would you?)  As for my experience. I am very pleased to be able to enjoy the Milk n’jas that I ordered when they were first starting off. Coupled with some Japanese style savory crepes. (Which is different from French style crepes. Ask the manager about it when he’s not busy running around and working those kinks out. Pretty interesting) I will say it’s nothing like the crepes I had in Japan. But we’re talking about Japanese style crepes from japan. Yeah, there’s gonna be a difference but for the fresh local farmers phinista gets their ingredients from it definitely doesn’t lose ground. My group also got a sweet crepe and I personally can not comment on it because I’m not a big fan of sweet food. My friends did say it tasted so good so you’ll have to go off of their judgement.  All in all I’m jealous it’s not closer to me but the residents around Fenway will be glad to see how they tell their story after the dust settles and they are at 100%.

I’m not one to go to a Cafe and buy coffee, as I enjoy brewing my own cold brew. However, I heard Neighborhood was under new management and I wanted to check it out. Immediately, I was greeted by the owner and he walked me through the menu. He even gave me samples of the different roasts he had. Vietnamese coffee truly has such an amazing and unique taste I’m dying to buy a bag of their beans. I’ve been here two days in a row and he still remembers my name. Phinista will have my business!
Very friendly young owners. Cold delicious drinks come in mason jar’s. Even to go with deposit. Come by and check it out!

Under new management, Neighborhoods has lowered its prices, sped up service, and still offering delicious espresso. This morning I was amazed by Vietnamese coffee I bought by the pound yesterday. The owner brought it outside especially for me when I saw my friend on the sidewalk. Definitely worth a stop!

Once I heard that Neighborhoods Cafe would be replaced by Phinista, I was bummed but excited to see what the new cafe would bring to the Fenway community. After checking out the new spot, I've had a chance to think through the below:  1. One thing that makes the Peterborough strip of restaurants so special is the true sense of community (in the center of a busy city). The restaurants that thrive in this area are the ones that foster this value and prioritize it. Walking into Phinista, the owner was working behind the counter but never made an effort to get to know the customers who asked about the new menu, ordered, and waiting for their food/drinks. When one customer ordered a regular drip coffee, I overheard the owner say they don't sell that. They warm up cold coffee with the milk steamer;  I watched this customer pour his coffee out in the trash. How can you be a coffee shop and not brew hot coffee throughout the day (especially when half of the community/your new customers are 60+ years old or students)?  2. The crepe was super delicious. And I'm sure that the ingredients used are fresh and made in house. But for two drinks and two crepes, it was $40. I don't think there was one coffee drink on the menu under $5 (and again, they don't even have hot drip coffee or flavored lattes). Also, they got rid of the classic bee stinger drink and sweet simplicity (chocolate hazelnut crepe), which the old cafe had as their most popular menu items. I also did not see a vegan crepe on the menu.  3. What happened to the amazing playlists from Neighborhoods cafe? Sounds like a small item but music makes a huge difference. Here, it felt like I was sitting in an elevator.  Overall, the main residents here are young adults and older folks. It seems like Phinista is trying to replicate their South Boston business model in a completely different environment with a very different audience.  Fenway doesn't need another Tatte, Cafe Nero, or Pavement. It needs another cafe that cares about the people it serves at a personal level. Where the owner knows the names of his customers and is willing to be authentic/unique but also familiar.
Excellent food, wonderful drinks, and outstanding service!
Warm and welcoming staff and the BEST coffee and crepes on the Sharone Hardesty

Neighborhood's was a staple of my fiance's and mine before covid. The staff and management has always been exceedingly lovely, the cafe is aesthetically brilliant, the coffee is delicious, and the crepes are exactly like the ones I had growing up in Europe. Neighborhood's is one of the first establishments we thought about when covid hit as well, we hoped that such a essential part of our city life would be okay.  Today, I surprised my fiance with crepes and coffee that we ate on our porch while watching dogs and kids in the park across the street. I had time to relax and reflect. The coffee was perfect. He had a London Fog iced latte and I the house shakerato.  I had the Tuscan Chicken Crepe which was delicious and he had the Strawberry Patch. The whipped cream had melted in his but we had cream that I whipped up as extra, and it honestly would have been delicious without it.  Thank you, Neighborhood's, for your continued dedication to being the little something extra that makes this city a part of our happiness.
This place is incredible,The owner Betsy is great.High quality customer service I went here today for the first time.There coffee is excellent 5 stars
Lovely coffee shop serving delicious crepes made with local produce! The owner was there and she was very attentive :)
Good coffee, clean seating area, and reasonable prices. Better atmosphere than Nero or Pavement, but not as much seating.
Delicious crepes. Small place that seems to be popular among the locals.
Best cafe in the Fenway!

The staff at Neighborhoods is the best! Even though it’s in the city, it still has the feel of local neighborhood (if you will) coffee shop. The crepes are homemade and delicious. My favorite latte is the bee stinger but my go-to there is Iced Coffee. They have some great iced coffee. The shop itself is small with some seating, but not a ton. The WiFi is also limited. It’s great if you don’t need WiFi or are only planning to sit for a bit.
Great for breakfast
Yummy crepes & great coffee! I had the golden latte 😋
A walking distance from the museum of fine arts. The place has a friendly atmosphere and great crepes. Coffee was good as well.
Cute little crepe cafe. Coffee is very good, crepe delicious, though the crepe is a bit small for the price. Can be crowded during the weekend brunch time.
Chillest breakfast in Fenway, good too!
Delicious crepes and a top-notch Spanish latte!
Friendly place, greets everyone who comes in the door.
This place is great! I love how it's open early enough to go there before class and the coffee is very good. Crepes are what they do best though! I highly reccomend The Tudor or the Jammin'.
Great coffee & subway tiled decor! 👍🏻👍🏻👍🏻
I ordered a strawberry marmalade crepe and a blueberry matcha. The woman at the cashier was friendly and the service was speedy. I will come back.
Stumbled by this place on accident and had an amazing experience. We had a great breakfast before walking to Fenway Park!
Delicious food, great service, and the bathroom is well-maintained.
Super cute, outdoor and indoor seating — yummy crepes and coffee!! Friendly staff, welcoming interior. Highly recommend!
Their food is very tasty but the price for one crepe is too high.
I loved their crepes and the atmosphere of the shop! Very cozy.
The perfect cup of coffee.
Yum! Great food and coffee!
Currently one of my favorite places to grab coffee and breakfast on the weekends. Nice outdoor seating, great coffee, and the crepes are amazing.
Crepes are fresh-made and delicious. Very friendly service as well

I ordered a crepe and a cup of latte "after eating the crepe," and the barista served both at the same time. I lightly claimed and the barista just told me "I was told so" with an aggressive attitude and no apologies. Overpriced for this level of service.  Observing the other customers while I was sitting there for an hour, I saw many people feeling frustrated due to the slow service and no care of waiting customers. I don't know if this was the problem of the person in duty today or the store itself. I can pay $5 for a crepe even the service is poor, but definitely not $11+tip...
The crepes and the muffins are really good, the cofee is good too, but they were very slow both times I went there.

Coffee and crepes were delicious. One of the only places I've been to where their drip coffee tastes exactly like it smells. Kudos to them. Never found a place that could get it that close. Would highly recommend
Love this place. Still delicious and coffee is fantastic!
Best crepes I've tried so far. They are just delicious.

This place has a unique charm. Located between some of the very popular eating spots in the Fenway neighborhood, Neighborhoods manages to stand apart. The coffee is great and I loved the spinach and feta croissant as well. The crepes are their signature items and I’ll make sure to visit again to savor them.

(Translated by Google) Coffee shop offering different types of coffee + crepe with different fruits. There is no external session. Traffic in some days. Respectful employees.  (Original) مقهى يقدم اصناف مختلفة من القهوة + الكريب بالفواكه مختلفة. توجد جلسة  خارجية . زحمة في بعض الايام. العاملون محترمين.
The crepes are very tasty, always freshly made. Nice atmosphere and location along side several other eateries.
Great coffee!

This place was recommended by one of the clerks at the Elizabeth Stewart Gardner Museum. We thought it was pretty great though the seating was limited inside and outside. As a result, we ended up sitting at the outdoor seating for the Thai restaurant next door. One of the employees recommended the Spanish Latte, which was good just like the rest of our order. It is hard to get coffee wrong and this place did it right. The order was prepared in a timely manner and all of the staff were courteous and helpful when faced with questions about the menu. We didn't order them but the crepes looked fantastic and tantalizing. Sadly we had already made our food plans for the day and didn't get a chance to try them.

I have been here a few times, but my most recent visit is what has finally pushed me to write this review. I went in with 3 friends early on a Saturday morning to get crepes and coffee on a day with fairly "standard" seeming business, a few people in line, inside seating full, but outside seating empty. We each ordered a different coffee and crepe and then proceeded to wait 50 minutes total before all 4 of us had our food and drinks. I was the first to order and got a crepe and a drip coffee, a drink that could have been handed to me as I paid; instead I waited 20 minutes directly in front of the barista and then finally made the first move and asked her if my coffee would be out soon. It took a further 5 minutes before she got around to pouring the drip coffee out of the carafe behind the bar for me. The food itself is okay, nothing special, but combined with the absurd lack of any sort of sense of urgency in any of the staff and the regular mistakes and seeming lack of training, it is a miracle to me that this place is still open. Not only do they need to invest more into hiring and training, they also need more inside seating, more crepe makers (only 2 currently which is part of the reason it takes sooo long to get your food), and price cut to multiple menu items. I would only eat here again if it was visibly empty and fully staffed and even then I would be wary of the amount of time I'd be taking out of my day for a mediocre meal.
Great atmosphere. Didn’t try the food but excellent cup of coffee and wonderful place to sit and enjoy it
So good!
Friendly staff and good gluten free crepes. There are vegan options as well. Good lattes
Tasty crepes and great coffee.

EDIT: Became horrendously slow. The workers are taking their sweet time. 45 minutes to make a raspberry crepe. Never used to be this slow. Just wish I could cancel my order and leave but I already paid. Old review: Love this place. Delicious drinks and crepes.
The food is really good.
This place does a very brisk business with the morning commuters. A big piece of that is their super-convenient location but the other part is that they simply serve excellent coffee very quickly.
The crapes are very good

Crepes were good! Got the Lemon & Sugar and Nutella and Banana (forgot the name). Only complaint is that maybe they're a bit too expensive given the ingredients and the preparation (which also took quite a bit longer than expected, even without the place being busy).

Cappuccino is sour and over burned, both of us wanted to throw it away immediately. Meanwhile it is $3.75+tax! And the cup is very small. Crepes are ok. There are only 6 tables here, for 2 person each. And since students are always sitting and studying here with their laptops and phones, there is not many chances one finds a vacant table to eat crepes. However if you take away the crepes, and heat up them the next day, they aren't very tasty. Also it takes quite some time here to make crepes for you, so be prepared to wait.
Lovely environment and good food and coffee but a little expensive
Great George Howell cappuccino. I really appreciate when a cafe that serves food puts an effort into their coffee drinks and this place had an excellent cappuccino.

Small place with a cozy atmosphere and quick service. Really enjoyed the savory crepe I had (Tuscan), and the coffee is good (George Howell sourced). Portions are just right for brunch, though a bit small for the price. It's not mind-blowing, but I'd definitely recommend it
Imagine the perfect place for a coffee and crepe, the staff is gentle and polite also you can even print if you need, best food in Fenway!!!

Didn't have the best experience and then had a mistake on my takeout order, but the staff were friendly and the food was good. I called and asked for a partial refund which they agreed to and apologized. I know stuff like that happens so I would give them another try and update my review if my experience was better.  UPDATE: After seeing my feedback they issued me a full refund, which I appreciated. Thanks Betsy!

Horrible place at first it looks nice and cozy. But looks may be deceiving. I ordered strawberry and banana Nutella crepes and they didn’t even use real Nutella and the strawberry’s were as if you melted them and cooked them they were very soggy. The coffee was horrible my dad took a couple of sips and threw it away mind this never happens. The service was even worse we tried to order a breakfast crepe but they said sorry we can’t after 10. Shortly he took a couple of orders of breakfast crepes from the people behind us and started making them. We asked why are u making it for them. He said it was a mistake and gave us a look and completely dismissed us. I don’t know how this place is four stars the food was horrible, the service was horrible, and the coffee was horrible. Would never recommend going here ever. Worst crepes I’ve ever had.

I'm not sure how this place gets an average of four stars.  My bad experience started with asking for a breakfast crepe, but the guy at the register told me that they stopped serving breakfast at 10AM only to proceed and take an order from the people that ordered the same exact egg and cheese breakfast crepe right after me.  I asked him about it and he rudely said with an attitude that it was a mistake and dismissed me; he said they were too busy to make an exception even though there was only one order after mine.  I tried to put this rude experience behind me and enjoy my coffee and Strawberry-Banana Nutella crepe, but the chocolate spread they used was not real Nutella and the strawberries were over cooked.  The coffee was so bad I threw away my cup shortly after a few sips.  A combination of bad service and below average crepes is not a good combination.  I never gave a place 2 stars, but this one deserves it.

My son brought me here for breakfast, and it was fabulous! They went above and beyond to accommodate my request for a keto version. 😃
Cute atmosphere, with good service. No wait, and polite service. I recommend the hot americano coffee- definitely has a coffee taste compared to most of the other places.
Solid sweet and savory crepes with top-notch coffee! One of the few coffee shops offering beans worthy of purchase and brews that need no condiments.

Comfort food and settings, ideal for an early morning breakfast, little available sitting space but somewhat cozy and intimate.

Sooo good... crepes are amazing and their seasonal drinks are amazingly delicious. Recommend pumpkin chai for fall and Fenway breeze in summer.

Cozy café, with some seating. They claim to have wifi, but they only offer xfinity wifi for one hour. Unfortunately, you can only use the free xfinity wifi once per month, so if you have already used your monthly allotment you are out of luck. Otherwise, this is a great place to come grab a quick coffee. Espresso was great!
Amazing food, amazing people. There are gluten free and vegan options, and the flavors are wonderful. Everything was fresh and the coffee was on-point. Instagramability: 10/10
Their savoury and sweet crepes are delicious! A must try if you want to have breakfast or brunch!

The most amazing place to eat. I would move to Boston just to eat a crepe here every day! Best breakfast I’ve had by far. If you’re in Boston I would seriously recommend order the sweet simplicity crepe for desert and egg turkey bacon and cheese crepe for breakfast.
It was delicious!!! Try the savory sweetness and Tuscan chicken. The iced coffee and the fenway breeze were also delicious. A must we will be back.😊 Comfortable atmosphere and friendly staff.

Good food! Loving the latte art, but was a little disappointed when one of the staffs were yelling. Dear, we didnt kill your mother, we are just coming here to enjoy and bring up your income, so please stop yelling
Nice place to grab a bite or drink coffee and do some work

Great crepes and coffee.

One of the most charming places in the area. Great crepes, pastries, coffee and coffee drinks, and very friendly staff. A lot of organic, and local?, ingredients which is great to see. Very glad there are vegan and gluten free options now too, and hope there will be more of them. Keep up the good work:)
Coze crape cafe. Sweet Ricotta cheese crape was unreal. Pleasant staff. Definitely recommend. :)
The food here was delicious and the service was good. This is a great place for a sit-down breakfast, if a little too small and crowded at times. The freshly made crepes are worth It though!
Outdoor seating is good. Indoors were a bit unclean when we visited. Otherwise drinks in general tasted better than Starbucks and were significantly cheaper as well!
Courteous staff, great atmosphere & aesthetic with prices that could beat any chain. Skip Starbucks and tatte, this is the place for coffee and the crepes can’t be beat.
Great, cozy shop with a great atmosphere, welcoming staff and delicious coffee. Best of all, the crepes. Try the Tuscan Chicken crepe. Fantastic every time.
Best coffee in Boston. Friendly staff and the most delicious crêpes!
Beautiful little cafe. Makes a great almond milk latte which was lovely during my Whole30. I appreciated that their almond milk didn't have added sugar 🙂 whole30 approved cafe!

Great for a quick stop or for a morning/afternoon work session. It's a small cozy place so if you want to hang out inside, you gotta get there quick. Their menu is awesome, especially if you want something to satisfy any cravings for sweets or baked goods. I can't wait to come back!
Great local coffee shop. Neighborhoods has a mellow vibe, good coffee and snacks, and is refreshingly pretention-free. Great place to get some work done or share tasty treats.

Just had the best almond milk cappuccino of my life here! Great vibe great staff. Unique and spicy coffee.

Checked out this place because a friend of mine told me it was a gem. I loved the iced latte that I got, as it was very well made. While the location is a little small, I still felt nice and cozy as I sat and enjoyed my drink. Loved watching the staff make the crepes too! Will be trying one on my next visit :)
Great coffee and crepes

Very friendly staff. The crepes are yummy and the coffee tastes like it should. It tends to be crowded because it's such a small space. Maybe sits 8-10 people indoors. They have outdoor seating which is nice when the weather is warmer! Another plus is that they have games and books to peruse.

The sweet crepe we ordered was stuffed with banana and topped with chocolate which was also quiet nice. A general comment on the crepes is that you have to ask for them to be cooked well done if you don’t like it very soft. The staff are friendly and they have an outdoor area too which overlooks a small park.

My personal favorites are the sweet crepes which I love grabbing after dinner out with friends as a little treat. Highly recommend this place for anyone who loves crepes!
Great coffee and crepes. Super cool staff and excellent service.

I've been going to Neighborhoods regularly for a few years now. I love their Spanish lattes, London Fog tea latte, and sweet crepes the most! The Tudor with apples and the new blueberry with mascarpone are delightful. The people behind the counter are exemplary.
Great crepes. Coffee from George Orwell well prepared in a La Marzocco machine with a Mythos grinder. They also do batch brews and French press.

Super cute, cozy creperie and cafe! They have great sweet crepes and savory crepes as well as other baked goodies in a pastry case, so it's a good spot for breakfast, lunch, or a quick snack. For drinks, there are a good selection of teas and coffee options. My favs include Croque Monsieur and The Tudor for crepes and the Beestinger and the Rooibus Fog for drinks. There are also usually fun seasonal options for crepes and drinks too! The only downsides to Neighborhoods are that there are only a few inside tables so seating is limited (and they're pretty popular), and the crepes are a bit expensive (though rightfully delish!) It's a great spot and I go there most of the time when I want to go out for breakfast!

Great place to get a beautiful cup of coffee (yes, coffee can be beautiful) and sit outside to people watch. Quiet and chill enough to read a book too. Delicious desserts too!

Coffee is great, pastries hit the spot, the atmosphere is what does it. Friendly staff, cool tunes and a semi-lively street to either sit in or sit out. Very nice coffee shop, there should be more like this one.
I wish I had gotten a desert but I was just too stuffed.  The hot cocoa was good at the start, but the end became similar to dunks in that I had to keep stirring it or it was too thick.
This is a great place to stop by for breakfast or lunch. Service is good and I've never had a bad crepe here. There are enough dessert/vegetarian options. It's a very cute cafe and worth stopping by.

I've loved this place ever since my first visit there back in October. Great service, delicious food, and perfectly made drinks make this a classic place for all of the college and grad students in the area to come and unwind.  As someone who cannot stand the bitter taste of coffee, I can't really comment on their more traditional coffee offerings. However, their Bee Stinger (iced or hot) is absolutely amazing while delivering the caffeine that I often so desperately need. If you are feeling something hot, then try the London Fog. Essentially, its Earl Grey Tea but amplified to its fullest potential.  Food-wise, you can't go wrong with a crepe from here. Sweet or savory, they are all quite good and def worth the money. My three staples are the Tudor, the Billy, and the Sweet Simplicity and I have never had a complaint. All are made to order and the people making them are clearly masters at what they do.  Speaking of service, everyone is very friendly and knowledgeable. The atmosphere here is very much the type you'd find in a local college town coffee shop though I''ll note that the place is very jammed packed with people, meaning that you will most certainly have a seat.  Clearly, this place remains to be one of the better kept secrets of the Fenway area.

We moved to town about a year ago and needed a coffee place that wasn't DD or SB.  This place just smells fantastic!  You can smell the freshly ground, high quality beans before you even open the door.  The owner ties time to source fair trade and naturally grown products to serve their customers.  I really appreciate that.  They now have the Chemex pour over and my husband practically salivates thinking about it...  Additionally, they offer a gluten free option for their crepes.  Love them - seriously, get the Tuscan Chicken.  If you love pesto you will love this!  Want your crepe a little more crispy - you say the word!  Also, they have a nice clean bathroom.  I wish they had a changing station but the floor is never dirty so I put the changing pad on that.  The staff is very friendly and its nice and bright.  The sun does come in like a death ray at 9am if you sit in the front window.  They also have outdoor seating Its nice to sit there and hear the roar of Fenway and the Red Sox in the summer.
Coffee is good but crepe is mediocre at best. Nice atmosphere for hanging out with a cup of coffee and a book, but I won't be back for a crepe.

I'm torn on giving Neighborhood's a good review for the sole reason of wanting to keep this wonderful place to myself. It's my a great spot for everything from a quiet afternoon with a book to a date.

They're never going to make it like this. The food was decent although the turkey bacon was barely cooked in the turkey bacon crepe. The French press coffee was excellent. The service, however, is abysmal. The staff spent most of their time gossiping and chatting with each other and a couple regular customers. The woman who took our order forgot half the things we ordered and then didn't put nuts in its oatmeal as requested. The coffee guy took forever to bring mugs and cream because he was talking and then forgot the sugar. When bringing our food, the crepe maker forgot which plate was which because she was talking up a storm, she even told us she was chatting. I want to like this place because it's local and cute, but the management needs to give the team a strong warning or fire everyone and start over.

The people here are amazing, very friendly.  What really gets me is the coffee, I've been around Boston to many different coffee shops in Brighton, back bay, Cambridge and downtown. This is one of my favorite places, they get their coffee from a local company in MA.  If you go try the house drip or espresso both are killer.
